i went to see the doctor this morning and it was really annoying because we had to wait in the waiting room for like an hour and i had to wait in the doctor's office for the doctor for anothing 15 something minutes.  my aunt came with me because my mom was helping her friends do this thing up at parma.  they sort of got lost and i think she hit the side of the car.  my mom freaks out sometimes when she drives.  we were driving in the freeway and she swerved off the road right into the snow! it was kind of funny to me but i got really scared when she stasrted swerving on the road, i thought we were going to crash. she had to stop for a bit to catch her breath. well, anyway, back to the present. after my check up, me and auntie heda went to this place called joe's crab shack. mm.. school yesterday wasn't much fun, maybe because practically everyone was sick and no one really had a lot of energy.  but after school was a lot of fun.  me, sarah, jamal, sandra and mike went to this chinese place to eat.  mike was supposed to pick up sandra and it took us a while to find her house.  when we got there, sandra was waiting outside looking icepopsicley.  we finally got to the chinese place at 8 or 7:45.  we hung out at my place after eating and we sat around and talked and laughed.  i thought it was gonna be boring but it actually turned out to be fun.

 yay!  i finally have that book i wanted to read.

today was pretty much the same as every other day.. we went to see hotel rwanda and it was a pretty good movie. it was really sad, and i think i would have cried a lot if i was watching it alone or if i wasnt sitting beside jamal who made me laugh a couple of times during the movie.  i had a lot of fun eating lunch with jamal, sandra, sarah, susan, robert and mike.  as usual, i went to the library with jamal, robert and ashley. no one could pick us up today so we just walked over to robert's place where i met his boxer/beagle named rocky.  he looks so funny, he has a skinny body and huge eyes. lol  idk, you have to actually see him to appreciate his comic look. mm.. i dont remember anything else taht happened today that's worth writing about.. byeeeee!!!

dont forget the welcome to duloc song!

welcome to duloc such a perfect town. here we have some rules let us lay them down. don't make waves, stay in line and we'll get along fine. duloc is the perfect place. please keep off of the grass, shine your shoes, wipe your ass. duloc is, duloc is, duloc is the perfect place!!

just got back from my aunt's.. her husband gave me a massage and i feel a whole lot better now.  i just hope that tomorrow ill look sick enough for my mom to let me stay home.. *sigh.. apparently i didnt inherit my gullibility from her

>>i was going to update during 6 period when we were in the computer lab but i ran out of time because the petrick had us do this spasnish activity or whatever.. she called me janet again today, ive decided not to bother telling her it's JANETTE because she'll just make the same mistake agian. 

>>we watched this film in government about this guy who defends himself for not stopping his friend from raping and killing this 7 yr old kid.. and he just sounded so stupid.  i might watch these movies i borrowed from the library tomorrow because i think i might be staying home.. my mom, bless her soul, is going to let me.  im gonna finish watching this old movie called persuasion, it's a book by jane austen that they turned into a movie.. im too lazy to read the book so i just rented the movie.

>>i can't wait to watch hotel rwanda on thursday!  it should be good, everyone who's seen it said so.  i just hope that they'll let us sit where ever we want to.. it would suck if i had to sit all by myself.

>>im talking to my aunt back in the philippines right now and she has her webcam on.  my new baby cousin looks so cute! she's really chubby, she has like 3 creases on her arms and her eyes are huge! lol.  i wish i had a picture of her.

>>im all alone at home right now, my mom and aunt are working and they wont be home till 11 something.. sometimes even 12.  jamal says i have a lot of opportunities to do wild stuff because they get home late.  i just might one of these days.. lol

>>im gonna go now, i have to go upstairs and help my aunt activate her cell phone's voice mail.  till tomorrow or the day after that!

not much happened today. not very exciting for a first entry. im not sure if anything very interesante happened today.. except mrs. petrick's class which never ceases to wake me up.  there was a fight in the e room but that wasnt very interesting to me because i didnt see it. in my gov't class, we watched this film about the holocaust.  it was really bad.. the dead bodies they tossed in the trenches looked like rubbery chicken and they showed decapitated bodies with the heads in this small tub beside them.  i planned to finish watching this movie i borrowed but my aunt barged in on my privacy so i just quit watching and scarfed down on my chocolates with her.  well anyway, my other aunt is on the phone with her friend laughing like a maniac.. im gonna go to the other room and try to restrain her.. adios and buenos noches!
